Why this license
----------------
The published statistics are derived from third-party exposure datasets, and
the most restrictive of them govern what any derivative can be: the GEM
Global Exposure Model is CC BY-NC-SA 4.0 (share-alike + non-commercial) and
GAR15 is distributed under UNISDR/UNEP-GRID non-commercial terms. This
repository therefore adopts CC BY-NC-SA 4.0 as a whole so its outputs comply
with those upstream terms.

Third-party data notices
------------------------
The underlying datasets remain under their own licenses; using this
repository's outputs also requires complying with them:

- GAR15 (GEG-15): UNISDR / UNEP-GRID, non-commercial use.
  De Bono & Chatenoux (2015).
- GIRI Building Exposure Model: UNEP/GRID-Geneva.
  Piller, Benvenuti & De Bono (2023).
- GEM Global Exposure Model (v2023.1.1, v2026.0.0): GEM Foundation,
  CC BY-NC-SA 4.0. Yepes-Estrada et al. (2023). Unit construction costs via
  the UCC-database compilation of the same model.
- Overture Maps buildings: ODbL 1.0 and source-specific licenses
  (OpenStreetMap contributors, Microsoft, Google and others).
- Global Building Atlas LoD1: TU Munich. Zhu et al. (2025),
  https://doi.org/10.5194/essd-17-6647-2025.
- Microsoft GlobalML Building Footprints: ODbL 1.0.
- GHSL (Built-up Volume, DEGURBA): European Commission JRC, CC BY 4.0.
- World Bank Official Boundaries and WDI indicators: CC BY 4.0.

Aggregated ADM1 statistics derived from ODbL sources are published with
attribution as produced works; the full building-level databases are not
redistributed here.
